The incumbent chairman of Abuja Municipal Area Council (AMAC), Abdullahi Adamu of All Progressives Congress, APC, has been declared winner of the area council election. He won with a margin of 17,785 votes. The area council returning officer, Prof Muhammadu Umaru Ndagi of Department of Linguistics, University of Abuja, said Adamu won after he polled a total votes of 53,538 to defeat his main opponent Princess Vivian Anazodo of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) who polled 35, 753 votes. 2019: Candido, Isokariari clinch AMAC APC, APGA tickets Council polls: APC candidate calls for unity FCT poll:  APC, PDP pick chairmanship candidates